import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    seattle_precipitation = data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']['precipitation']
    new_york_precipitation = data[data['location'] == 'New York']['precipitation']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot([seattle_precipitation, new_york_precipitation], labels=['Seattle', 'New York'])
    ax.set_ylabel('Precipitation')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of precipitation in Seattle and New York?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    seattle_data = data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']
    seattle_data = seattle_data[['date', 'temp_max', 'temp_min']]
    seattle_data = seattle_data.set_index('date')
    seattle_data.plot(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.title('How does the temperature vary over time in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Maximum Temperature', 'Minimum Temperature'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['date'])
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data['weather'] = data['weather'].astype('category')
    data = data.groupby(['location', 'weather']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    seattle_data = data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']
    ny_data = data[data['location'] == 'New York']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(seattle_data['weather'], seattle_data['counts'], label='Seattle')
    ax.bar(ny_data['weather'], ny_data['counts'], label='New York')
    ax.set_xlabel('Weather')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common type of weather in Seattle and New York?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    seattle_data = data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']
    seattle_data = seattle_data[['temp_max', 'precipitation']]
    seattle_data = seattle_data.dropna()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(seattle_data['precipitation'], seattle_data['temp_max'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Precipitation')
    ax.set_ylabel('Maximum Temperature')
    ax.axvline(seattle_data['precipitation'].median(), color='red', label='Median Precipitation: {:.2f}'.format(seattle_data['precipitation'].median()))
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('How does precipitation affect temperature in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
